  "text": "An indirect experimental determination of the diffusion boundary layer thickness showed that for particles, 0.53 to 5.9 μ m, the effective diffusion boundary layer, h EFF , was directly proportional to the particle diameter for the smaller particles. Moreover, the dissolution rate is indirectly proportional to the square of the particle diameter [CITATION_1] .",
